SIMPLE: planchette
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Planchette
<hw>Plan`chette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Planchet</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A circumferentor. See
<er>Circumferentor</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small tablet of wood supported on casters and
having a pencil attached. The characters produced by the pencil on
paper, while the hand rests on the instrument and it is allowed to move,
are sometimes translated as of oracular or supernatural
import.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Planching</ent>⟦br⟧
